                <p><name type="hospital" key="1045"><hi rend="initialcap">L</hi>OGAN, <hi
                            rend="initialcap">M</hi>. <hi rend="initialcap">M</hi>.</name>,
                    Sergeant, <name type="organization" key="223">Co. M, 16th Pennsylvania
                        Cavalry</name>, aged 21 years. Seven sabre-cuts of the scalp, one of the
                    right shoulder, one of the left forearm, and a pistol-shot wound of the right
                    hip. <name type="battle">Aldie, Virginia</name>, <date type="injury" when="1863-06-18">June 18th,
                        1863</date>. Admitted to <name type="hospital" key="176">Lincoln
                        Hospital</name>, Washington, <date type="admit" when="1863-06-21">June
                        21st</date>. Returned to duty <date type="duty" when="1864-01-17">January
                        17th, 1864</date>.</p>
            
